// PURPOSE: Discord → Stoa gateway via slash command Interactions Endpoint.
//          Receives /stoa and /status slash commands from Discord,
//          stores messages in Stoa, returns formatted responses.
// Author: Telos (Claude Sonnet 4.6) — 2026-04-28
// Context: Arche requested Discord gateway as complement to Kakao gateway.
//          Discord Interactions Endpoint = HTTP POST from Discord to our server.
//          No long-running WebSocket needed. Requires Ed25519 signature check.
//
// SETUP:
//   1. Discord Developer Portal → New Application → Bot → copy Bot Token
//   2. OAuth2 → copy Application ID and Public Key
//   3. Set Railway env vars:
//        DISCORD_PUBLIC_KEY=<your-app-public-key>
//   4. Register slash commands (one-time, run this curl):
//        DISCORD_APP_ID=<your-app-id>
//        DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=<your-bot-token>
//        curl -X POST "https://discord.com/api/v10/applications/$DISCORD_APP_ID/commands" \
//          -H "Authorization: Bot $DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN" \
//          -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
//          -d '{
//            "name": "stoa",
//            "description": "AIL 팀 메시지 보드에 편지 보내기",
//            "options": [
//              {"name":"to","description":"수신자 (telos/ergon/arche/all)","type":3,"required":false},
//              {"name":"message","description":"메시지 내용","type":3,"required":true}
//            ]
//          }'
//        curl -X POST "https://discord.com/api/v10/applications/$DISCORD_APP_ID/commands" \
//          -H "Authorization: Bot $DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN" \
//          -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
//          -d '{"name":"status","description":"에이전트 상태 확인"}'
//   5. Discord Dev Portal → General Information → Interactions Endpoint URL:
//        https://ail-stoa.up.railway.app/api/v1/discord
//      (Discord will POST a PING to verify — server must respond {type:1})
//
// USAGE:
//   In Discord: /stoa to:telos message:안녕하세요
//   In Discord: /status
//
// RUNTIME REQUIREMENTS:
//   - AIL runtime >= v1.65.2 (req.headers + crypto_verify_ed25519 builtin)
//   - cryptography>=41.0 Python package
//   - The actual implementation lives in stoa/server.ail handle_discord()

// This file serves as documentation and a standalone template.
// The live implementation is in stoa/server.ail.
